Delta Force saw hell on Wednesday at the ongoing Mark D’Ball Men’s Basketball Championship and weathered an early game onslaught from the Kada Stars before fighting back to win 67-63 points to confirm their participation in the Top-16 of the Championship. The Kada boys dunked to a 14 points lead and appeared confident to spring an upset against their illustrious opponents at the Indoor Hall, Package B of Moshood Abiola National Stadium, Abuja, but the determined Deltans rally the clock round the court to snatch victory. Delta Force shot into early lead 22-8 and 45-22 in the first and second quarters respectively, but could not maintain the wide margin lead as the Kada Stars levelled at 62-62. At the 62-62 scoreline, the Kada Stars officials and supporters boisterously romped into frenzy jubilation, perhaps believing it would be a repeat of their game against Novena Heartlanders of Imo state that they from 21 points deficit to out-dunk their opponent.The determined Delta Force players maintained their calm; a development that earned them the deserved victory at 67-63. In other matches decided yesterday, tournament favourite, Kano Pillars whitewash Novena Heartlanders 85-48 while Benue Braves beat Bauchi Nets 97-59.